 ing (COIL)\, Diplomacy Lab\, and more. Topics span disciplines and highli
 ght how IU students and faculty are turning learning into action on some 
 of today's most pressing global challenges.</p><p class="" data-start="15
 15" data-end="1579"><strong>All are welcomeŌĆöcome be inspired and join u
 s in shaping a more connected world!<br /><br />  Present Your Work at th
 e Poster Session<br /><br /></strong>Are you a student or instructor enga
 ged in global learning on an IU campus? We invite you to share your work 
 during the poster session! This is a great opportunity to showcase experi
 ential learning projects\, connect with others\, and highlight how global
  learning is happening right here in Indiana. Poster printing costs will 
 be covered.&#160\;<br /><br />  Please fill out this brief <a href="https
 ://iuglobal-fireform.eas.iu.edu/online/form/index/cgcgl002">interest form
 </a> if you would like to participate in the poster session.<br /><br /> 
  Questions?&#160\; Email <a href="mailto:global@iu.edu">global@iu.edu</a>
  with Global Learning Showcase in the subject line.<strong><br /></strong
 ></p><p class="" data-start="1581" data-end="1734"><strong data-start="15
 81" data-end="1598">Supported by:</strong> IU Global\, the Center for the
  Study of Global Change</p>
